<sec id="summary">
  <title>Summary</title>
  <p>sourmash is a toolbox for creating, comparing, and manipulating
  MinHash sketches of genomic data.</p>
  <p>MinHash sketches provide a lightweight way to store “signatures” of
  large DNA or RNA sequence collections, and then compare or search them
  using a Jaccard index. MinHash sketches can be used to identify
  samples, find similar samples, identify data sets with shared
  sequences, and build phylogenetic trees
  (<xref alt="Ondov et al., 2015" rid="ref-ondov2015fast" ref-type="bibr">Ondov
  et al., 2015</xref>).</p>
  <p>sourmash provides a command line script, a Python library, and a
  CPython module for MinHash sketches.</p>
</sec>
